OL,3,CSpeculation over Ryan Giggs return to
OL,4,CWales manager role
OL,6,FIf appointed, he would be Wales' first
OL,7,Fnon-Welsh manager in more than 20
OL,8,Fyears.
OL,10,FGary Speed's successor Chris Coleman,
OL,11,F54, first took the reigns of the Wales
OL,12,Fteam in 2012 and went on to guide the
OL,13,Fside to qualify for their first major
OL,14,Ftournament for 58 years: Euro 2016.
OL,16,FThe side reached the semi-finals but
OL,17,Fhe resigned as Wales manager the
OL,18,Ffollowing November after a home defeat
OL,19,Fto the Republic of Ireland ended hopes
OL,20,Fof Wales reaching the World Cup in
OL,21,F2018.
